page.title: 12NORTHWOOD
page.content: Northwood is a small village with two factories,which are its main features.It is mainly covered by houses,but there is some openwoodland. At the top of the square is an disused railway line,and in Paget's Place,the local pub,there is a working mens club ,originally built for the builders of the railway line. In Tinkersley area there there is a disused quarry named Parish quarry it is now an unofficial dumping ground. There is a farm in the area called Burly Field farm. There are some plantations in the area,but most of the land is grass or moorland.There are few houses in this area,they are based at the bottom left hand corner.
